  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Madara (Milk in Hausa)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Madara program meets the early recovery needs  in the department of Filingu&#xE9; in the Tillaberi region, through an integrated package of activities aimed at protecting animal assets and increasing dairy production in order to enhance food security and strengthen livelihoods. The program improves the purchasing power of impoverished households in the peri-urban and rural areas of Filingu&#xE9;, and diversify their diets and livelihoods activities to help them weather future shocks, as well as strengthen the milking cow dairy market system in the Filingu&#xE9; department in order to enhance livelihoods of actors in the value chain, and increase availability of affordable and nutritious dairy products for potentially food insecure households in the Filingu&#xE9; department, particularly during the lean seasons.</narrative>
  </description>
